Woman killed in shooting spree as she celebrated birthday with friends
Police have launched a murder inquiry after a shooting spree ahead of the Notting Hill Carnival left one woman dead as she celebrated her birthday. Police at the scene of a shooting in Kilburn High Road, north west London, where two women were shot, one fatally. Photo: PA	By David Barrett, Home Affairs Correspondent
1:40PM BST 24 Aug 2013
Follow Sabrina Moss, who turned 24 on Friday, and was out with friends in Kilburn High Road, north London, when she was shot dead in the early hours of Saturday. A senior detective said Miss Moss was believed to have been an innocent party who was "in the wrong place at the wrong time". The incident took place just two miles from the route of the carnival, which opens on Sunday. Another woman was injured but her injuries are not life-threatening, a Scotland Yard spokesman said. Det Ch Insp John Sandlin said: "Enquiries continue to establish the full circumstances of this tragic incident. Related Articles
